The Article 14 of the [[Albanian Constitution]] states that ''"The official language in the Republic of Albania is Albanian."''<ref>{{cite web|title=Constitution of the Republic of Albania |url=http://www.km.gov.al/skedaret/1231927768-Constitution%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20Albania.pdf |publisher=Republic of Albania Council of Ministers |accessdate=12 November 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120808194737/http://www.km.gov.al/skedaret/1231927768-Constitution%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20Albania.pdf |archivedate= 8 August 2012 |df= }}</ref> 
According to the 2011 population census, 2,765,610, 98.767% of the population declared [[Albanian language|Albanian]] as their mother tongue ("mother tongue is defined as the first or main language spoken at home during childhood").<ref>{{cite web|url=http://census.al/Resources/Data/Census2011/Instat_print%20.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-06-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120112022139/http://census.al/Resources/Data/Census2011/Instat_print%20.pdf |archivedate=2012-01-12 |df= }}</ref>

===Dialects===
Standard Albanian is based in the [[Tosk]] dialect, spoken in the south. [[Gheg]] is spoken in the north and also by [[Kosovo Albanians]]. The traditional border between the two dialects is the [[Shkumbin]] River. Although they are somewhat different, they are mutually intelligible.<ref name="Baker">{{cite book|last=Baker|first=Colin|title=Encyclopedia of bilingualism and bilingual education|year=1998|publisher=Multilingual Matters|location=Clevedon|isbn=9781853593628|author2=Jones, Sylvia Prys |page=412}}</ref><ref name="Baker"/><ref>{{cite book|last=Dana|first=Leo Paul|title=Economies of the Eastern Mediterranean region : economic miracles in the making|year=2001|publisher=World Scientific|location=Singapore [u.a.]|isbn=9789810244743|page=47}}</ref> Other notable varieties, all of which are sub-dialects of Tosk, include  [[Cham Albanian dialect|Cham]],  [[Arbereshe language|Arbereshe]] spoken in Italy and [[Arvanitic]] in Southern Greece.

==Minority languages==
