{{Refimprove|date=February 2014}} {{Infobox ethnic group| |group= White Angolan |image= |caption= |pop= Approx. 220,000 |popplace= {{flag|Angola}} (Approx. 220,000<ref name=cia/>) |langs= [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], [[Afrikaans]] |rels= [[Christianity]] (mainly [[Roman Catholicism]]) |related= [[White people in Botswana|White Botswanans]], [[White Namibians]], [[Afrikaners]] }}
There are light-skinned or '''White Angolans''' mostly '''Angolans of European descent''' most significantly from [[Portugal]]. This population also includes [[White Brazilians]] of European Ancestry. Additional white Angolans emigrated from [[Eastern Europe]] when the country was a [[People's Republic of Angola|communist republic]], in particular Russians and Poles. For a long time a significant community of [[Afrikaners]] lived in southern Angola, but most left in and after 1975.
Currently, Whites are a minority ethnic group in Angola, accounting for 1% of the country's population.<ref name=cia>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bc.html |title=CIA - The World Factbook -- Angola |accessdate=2014-01-31 |publisher=CIA | archiveurl= https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/ao.html| archivedate= 28 January 2014 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> The White population usually speaks [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]].<ref name=economist>{{cite web|title=Flight from Angola|url=http://www.economist.com/node/12079340|publisher=economist.com|accessdate=21 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=thisisafrica>{{cite web|last=Ahrens|first=Lula|title=Race relations in Angola|url=http://www.thisisafrica.me/opinion/detail/19594/race-relations-in-angola|publisher=thisisafrica.me|accessdate=21 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=mixedindifferentshades>{{cite web|title=Angola|url=http://www.mixedindifferentshades.net/africa/angola.html|publisher=mixedindifferentshades.net|accessdate=21 February 2014}}</ref>
